The article is a letter from former President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House, discussing the deployment of U.S. Armed Forces personnel to the Central African Republic. The purpose of this deployment is to support the activities of the U.S. Embassy in Bangui and to protect embassy personnel and property. The deployment is expected to be replaced by an augmented U.S. Marine Security Guard Detachment and additional civilian security personnel from the U.S. Department of State as the security situation allows. The action is taken to fulfill the President's responsibility to protect U.S. citizens both domestically and abroad, in line with national security and foreign policy interests. The letter is provided to keep Congress fully informed, as required by the War Powers Resolution.